TORCH012 [*] Use `.to("cpu")` instead of `.cpu()`
  --> TORCH012.py:11:10
   |
 9 | def to_device():
10 |     x = torch.tensor([1.0])
11 |     y1 = x.cpu()
   |          ^^^^^
12 |     y2 = x.cuda()
   |
help: Replace `.cpu()` with `.to("cpu")`
8  |
9  | def to_device():
10 |     x = torch.tensor([1.0])
   -     y1 = x.cpu()
11 +     y1 = x.to("cpu")
12 |     y2 = x.cuda()
13 |
14 |
note: This is an unsafe fix and may change runtime behavior

